== Bundles & Packs ==
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/Bundles & Packs|Bundles & Packs]] for more detailed information.''

Bundles & Packs are how content gets delivered to users. They appear in the Bundles & Packs tab, and once claimed, users will get rewarded with one or multiple of the content types. If users have multiple bundles or packs in their inventory, they can choose which one they want to open by clicking the arrow on either side of the menu.

Bundles & Packs can have an expiry date, in which users must claim before a certain date.

==Sharing==
[[File:Gallery_Photo&SharingExample.webp|200px|thumb|A photo inside a sharing pedestal.]]
VRC+ users can share photos, prints, emoji, stickers, and UI themes with other VRC+ within the same instance. Pressing the share button on the respective content type allows the user to drop a [[Sharing|sharing]] pedestal.

==Exclusives==
[[Special:MyLanguage/VRC+#Exclusives|VRC+ Exclusives]] is content that is only available for VRC+ supporters. Unlike Bundles, Exclusives are not claimable and automatically appear in user's inventories. Content that is "VRC+ Exclusive" is labeled with VRC+ logo in the top left corner.

== Collections ==
Emojis, stickers and items can belong to collections, which can be used to filter the Inventory.

List of known collections:

* Pride Month 2025
* Summer 2025

==Uploading==
User icons, photos, emoji, stickers, or prints can be taken and uploaded within the client via the [[Camera|camera's]] "Camera Mode" options. They can also be uploaded on the VRChat website via their respective pages.

* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/photos|Photos}}
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/user/me?settings{{=}}true|User Icons}} 
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/emojis/custom|Emoji}}
* {{VRC_link|https://vrchat.com/home/inventory/stickers/custom|Stickers}}

===Upload requirements===
[[File:DancingBirdSprite.png|200px|thumb|right|An example of a sprite sheet for a 10-frame animated emoji.]]
When uploading files to be used as user icons, photos, emoji, stickers, or prints, on the VRChat website, they must meet the following criteria:

*Must be less than 10MB
*Larger than 64x64 pixels
*Icons and Photos must be smaller than 2048x2048 pixels
*Emojis and Stickers must be smaller than 1024x1024 pixels

When uploading Animated Emoji, images should be 1024x1024 with square frames in a uniform grid, ordered left to right, then top to bottom. You can preset animation values in advance using the file name, like so'':''

*''ExampleEmoji_14frames_10fps.png''

The "Enable Sprite Sheet Mode" option must be checked for images to animate.

